</p>
<p>If this is your first Doctrine listener, welcome! They're pretty friendly. Here's the idea:
we'll create a function that Doctrine will call whenever <em>any</em> entity is inserted or updated.
That'll let us to do some work before that happens.</p>
<p>Implement an <code>EventSubscriber</code> interface and then use <code>Command</code>+<code>N</code> or the "Code"-&gt;"Generate"
menu, select "Implement Methods" and choose the one method: <code>getSubscribedEvents()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="5e4cedcdec">
