<p>When Doctrine calls this, it will pass you an object called <code>LifecycleEventArgs</code>,
from the ORM namespace.</p>
<p>This method will be called before <em>any</em> entity is inserted. How do we know <em>what</em>
entity is being saved? With <code>$entity = $args-&gt;getEntity()</code>. Now, if this is <em>not</em>
an <code>instanceof User</code>, just return and do nothing:</p>
