<h2 id="encoding-the-password">Encoding the Password <a class="headerlink" href="encoding-user-password#encoding-the-password" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Now, on to encoding that password.</p>
<p>Symfony comes with a built-in service that's really good at encoding passwords. It's
called <code>security.password_encoder</code> and if you looked it up on <code>debug:container</code>, its
class is <code>UserPasswordEncoder</code>. We'll need that, so add a <code>__construct()</code> function
and type-hint a single argument with <code>UserPasswordEncoder $passwordEncoder</code>. I'll hit
<code>Option</code>+<code>Enter</code> and select "Initialize Fields" to save me some time:</p>
