	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2937853526" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2937853526" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Ryan,</p><p>why don't you use the lifecycle callbacks right on the entity?<br>F.e.:</p><p>namespace AppBundle\Entity;</p><p>use Doctrine\ORM\Mapping as ORM;<br>use Symfony\Component\Validator\Constraints as Assert;</p><p>/**<br> * User<br> *<br> * @ORM\Table(name="user")<br> * @ORM\Entity()<br> * @ORM\HasLifecycleCallbacks()<br> */<br>class User<br>{</p><p>... fields and functions</p><p>    /**<br>     * @ORM\PrePersist()<br>     */<br>    public function prePersist()<br>    {<br>        // ... stuff to do before persist to database<br>    }</p><p>    /**<br>     * @ORM\PrePersist()<br>     */<br>    public function preUpdate()<br>    {<br>        // ... stuff to do before persist to database<br>    }<br>}</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
