	                                <p>Hey Yang!</p><p>That's a GREAT question - I hate when things are just magically shown - so shame on me :).</p><p>Of course, you can read the documentation. And, at the very least, you would probably need to read a little bit of documentation to *at least* know that there *is* an argument to this method. But, to know *what* class this is (i.e. that it is a LifecycleEventArgs), I like to simply dump() the variable to find out what it is:</p><p></p><pre><code><br>public function prePersist($event)<br>{<br>    dump($event);die; // what are you!?<br>}<br></code></pre><p></p><p>When in doubt, this is what I like to do!</p><p>Cheers!</p>
